'''彌生人'''（{{jpn|j=弥生人|hg=やよいじん|rm=Yayoi-jin}}），是指在[[彌生時代|彌生時代]]（西元前10世紀到西元3世紀）抵達[[日本列島|日本列島]]的移民集團<ref name="Silberman2012">Silberman et al., 154–155.</ref><ref name="SchirokauerBrown2012">Schirokauer et al., 133–143.</ref><ref name="Shinya">{{cite journal |url=http://www.seaa-web.org/bul-essay-01.htm |title=A Comment on the Yayoi Period Dating Controversy |journal=Bulletin of the Society for East Asian Archaeology |surname=Shōda |given=Shinya |year=2007 |volume=1 |access-date=2020-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190801234503/http://www.seaa-web.org/bul-essay-01.htm |archive-date=2019-08-01 |url-status=live }}</ref>，與[[繩文人|繩文人]]無論在文化上還是體質上都有明顯區別。兩群人(和後來的[[古墳人|古墳人]])融合成為現代日本人<ref>{{Cite web|title='Jomon woman' helps solve Japan's genetic mystery {{!}} NHK WORLD-JAPAN News|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/backstories/555/|website=NHK WORLD|language=en|access-date=2020-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200426044803/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/backstories/555/|archive-date=2020-04-26|url-status=live}}</ref>。

== 起源 ==

學術界就彌生人的起源提出了以下幾個假說:

* 目前最流行的假說為彌生人原居[[朝鮮半島|朝鮮半島]]或[[長江三角洲|長江三角洲]]並將[[水稻|水稻]]帶到日本列島<ref name="Sakitani">崎谷満『DNA・考古・言語の学際研究が示す新・日本列島史』(勉誠出版　2009年)(in Japanese)</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.trussel.com/prehist/news111.htm | title=Yayoi linked to Yangtze area | access-date=2018-02-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222044801/http://www.trussel.com/prehist/news111.htm | archive-date=2017-02-22 | url-status=live }}</ref>
* 另一個假說基於{{tsl|ja|土井ヶ浜遺跡|土井濱遺跡}}的遺骸與在朝鮮半島北部所找到的相似，以及在繩文時代晚期和彌生時代早期廣泛流行於西日本的{{tsl|ja|刻目突帯文土器|刻目突帶文陶器}}也在日本海西北岸、位於今[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]][[濱海邊疆州|濱海邊疆州]]的{{tsl|ja|シニガイ文化||シニ・ガイ文化}}中找得到而推斷彌生人原居於朝鮮半島北部<ref>[http://21coe.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/wfsection/article.php?articleid=66 ロシア極東新石器時代研究の新展開] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826072646/http://21coe.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/wfsection/article.php?articleid=66 |date=2017-08-26 }} (in Japanese)</ref>
* 多重族源論也越來越得到學術界支持，這個假說主要是根據考古、文化、習俗、語言上與東北亞、東亞、東南亞各地區族群的相似度，繼而推斷出彌生人根本不是單一族群而是多個不同的族群於不同的時間點抵達日本列島。<ref>徳永勝士 (2003)「HLA と人類の移動」『Science of humanity Bensei 』(42), 4-9, 東京：勉誠出版 (in Japanese)</ref><ref>岡正雄『異人その他 日本民族=文化の源流と日本国家の形成』 言叢社 1979 (in Japanese)</ref>
* [[澳大利亞|澳大利亞]]歷史學家安·庫馬爾（Ann Kumar）<ref group="note">{{cite web |url= https://researchers.anu.edu.au/researchers/kumar-al |title= Professor Ann Kumar |author= Director (Research Services Division) |date= 2019-07-20 |quote= Professor Ann Kumar, [[Bachelor_of_Arts|BA]] Hons ([[Australian_National_University|ANU]]), [[Doctor_of_Philosophy|PhD]] (ANU). Visiting Fellow. School of Culture, History & Language. ANU College of Asia and the Pacific. |access-date= 2019-07-20 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190720045232/https://researchers.anu.edu.au/researchers/kumar-al |archive-date= 2019-07-20 |url-status= live }}</ref>就遺傳學和語言學證據推斷有部份的彌生人是[[南島民族|南島民族]]<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.languagesoftheworld.info/historical-linguistics/javanese-influence-on-japanese.html |title=Javanese influence on Japanese - Languages Of The World |date=2011-05-09 |work=Languages Of The World |access-date=2018-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725122936/https://www.languagesoftheworld.info/historical-linguistics/javanese-influence-on-japanese.html |archive-date=2018-07-25 |url-status=live }}</ref>。
* 有些日本歷史學家如鳥越憲三郎、若林弘子等認為彌生人的祖先來自[[雲貴高原|雲貴高原]]<ref>鳥越憲三郎『原弥生人の渡来 』(角川書店,1982)、『倭族から日本人へ』(弘文堂 ,1985)、『古代朝鮮と倭族』(中公新書,1992)、『倭族トラジャ』(若林弘子との共著、大修館書店,1995)、『弥生文化の源流考』(若林弘子との共著、大修館書店,1998)、『古代中国と倭族』(中公新書,2000)、『中国正史倭人・倭国伝全釈』(中央公論新社,2004)</ref><ref group="note">{{cite web |url= https://researchmap.jp/read0049668/ |title= SUWA Haruo (諏訪春雄) |date= 2018-01-18 |access-date= 2021-06-12 |archive-date= 2022-01-21 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220121023531/https://researchmap.jp/read0049668/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>，而諏訪春雄則認為倭人為[[百越|百越]]的一支<ref>諏訪春雄編『倭族と古代日本』(雄山閣出版、1993)また諏訪春雄通信100</ref>。
* 俄裔美國語言學家亞歷山大·沃文（Vovin Alexander）認為彌生人原居朝鮮半島，後來起源於遼吉地區的古朝鮮民族南侵，繼而被驅趕和同化<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Janhunen |first=Juha |date=2010 |title=Reconstructing the Language Map of Prehistorical Northeast Asia |journal=Studia Orientalia |number=108 |pages=281–304 |quote=... there are strong indications that the neighbouring Baekje state (in the southwest) was predominantly Japonic-speaking until it was linguistically Koreanized.}}</ref><ref name=":1">Vovin, Alexander (2013). "From Koguryo to Tamna: Slowly riding to the South with speakers of Proto-Korean". ''Korean Linguistics''. '''15''' (2): 222–240.</ref>。約翰·惠特曼（John Whiteman）提出類似的觀點，認為彌生人與古朝鮮民族無關，但他們在[[無紋陶器時代|無紋陶器時代]]共同生活在朝鮮半島，有部份的彌生人大約在2950年前就遷移到日本列島，而在2300年前左右北方的古朝鮮民族才抵達朝鮮半島，起初與彌生人共存，後來將他們同化。雙方的語言互相影響，形成[[語言聯盟|語言聯盟]]，後來兩個語系內部的多樣性因[[奠基者效應|奠基者效應]]而減少<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Whitman|first=John|date=2011-12-01|title=Northeast Asian Linguistic Ecology and the Advent of Rice Agriculture in Korea and Japan|journal=Rice|volume=4|issue=3|pages=149–158|doi=10.1007/s12284-011-9080-0|issn=1939-8433|doi-access=free}}</ref>。

=== 基因 ===
彌生人的Y染色體主要為Haplogroup O-M176|單倍群O-M176（今約佔36%）、[[單倍群O-M122|單倍群O-M122]]（今約佔23%）和單倍群O-M119（今約佔4%），皆為典型的東亞和東南亞單倍群。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Nonaka|first1=I.|last2=Minaguchi|first2=K.|last3=Takezaki|first3=N.|date=2007|title=Y-chromosomal Binary Haplogroups in the Japanese Population and their Relationship to 16 Y-STR Polymorphisms|journal=Annals of Human Genetics|volume=71|issue=4|pages=480–495|doi=10.1111/j.1469-1809.2006.00343.x|pmid=17274803|issn=1469-1809|hdl=10130/491|s2cid=1041367|hdl-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Kutanan|first1=Wibhu|last2=Chakraborty|first2=Ranajit|last3=Eisenberg|first3=Arthur|last4=Sun|first4=Jie|last5=Chantawannakul|first5=Panuwan|last6=Ghirotto|first6=Silvia|last7=Pittayaporn|first7=Pittayawat|last8=Srikummool|first8=Metawee|last9=Srithawong|first9=Suparat|date=July 2015|title=Genetic and linguistic correlation of the Kra–Dai-speaking groups in Thailand|journal=Journal of Human Genetics|volume=60|issue=7|pages=371–380|doi=10.1038/jhg.2015.32|pmid=25833471|s2cid=21509343|issn=1435-232X}}</ref>。日本[[分子人類學家|分子人類學家]]{{tsl|ja|崎谷満|崎谷滿}}表示單倍群O1b2主要常見於日本人、朝鮮人和滿人，O1則在長江文明的男性身上找到。長江文明沒落後分成幾個部落分別向西和向北遷移，其中一支到達[[山東半島|山東半島]]、朝鮮半島和日本列島<ref>崎谷満『DNA・考古・言語の学際研究が示す新・日本列島史』(勉誠出版 2009年</ref>。有研究指單倍群01b1為[[南亞語系|南亞語系民族]]主要的父系血統與O1b2共為「泛南亞父系血統」（para-Austroasiatic）<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5Z5BDwAAQBAJ&q=japonic+austroasiatic&pg=PA207|title=Language Dispersal Beyond Farming|last1=Robbeets|first1=Martine|last2=Savelyev|first2=Alexander|date=2017-12-21|publisher=John Benjamins Publishing Company|isbn=9789027264640|access-date=2021-06-12|archive-date=2021-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210711070815/https://books.google.com/books?id=5Z5BDwAAQBAJ&q=japonic+austroasiatic&pg=PA207|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

現代大和民族主要是彌生人的後裔並與其他現代東亞族群都有關，特別是朝鮮人和漢人<ref>{{cite journal |author1= Siska, Veronika |author2= Jones, Eppie Ruth |author3= Jeon, Sungwon |author4= Bhak, Youngjune |author5= Kim, Hak-Min |author6= Cho, Yun Sung |author7= Kim, Hyunho |author8= Lee, Kyusang |author9= Veselovskaya, Elizaveta |author10= Balueva, Tatiana |author11= Gallego-Llorente, Marcos |author12= Hofreiter, Michael |author13= Bradley, Daniel G. |author14= Eriksson, Anders |author15= Pinhasi, Ron |author16= Bhak, Jong |author17= Manica, Andrea |title= Genome-wide data from two early Neolithic East Asian individuals dating to 7700 years ago |journal= [[Science_Advances|Science Advances]] |volume= 3 |issue= 2 |pages= e1601877 |url= |publication-date= February 1, 2017 |doi= 10.1126/sciadv.1601877 |pmid= 28164156 |pmc= 5287702 |bibcode= 2017SciA....3E1877S |year= 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20191224045038/https://advances.sciencemag.org/content/advances/3/2/e1601877.full.pdf |archive-date= December 24, 2019 |url-status= live }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1= Wang, Yuchen |author2= Lu Dongsheng |author3= Chung Yeun-Jun |author4= Xu Shuhua |title= Genetic structure, divergence and admixture of Han Chinese, Japanese and Korean populations |journal= Hereditas |volume= 155 |page= 19 |year= 2018 |url= |doi= 10.1186/s41065-018-0057-5 |pmid= 29636655 |pmc= 5889524 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180703050512/https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1186%2Fs41065-018-0057-5.pdf |archive-date= 2018-07-03 |url-status= live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Wang |first1=Yuchen  |last2= Lu |first2=Dongsheng |last3=Chung |first3=Yeun-Jun  |last4=Xu |first4=Shuhua |title=Genetic structure, divergence and admixture of Han Chinese, Japanese and Korean populations |journal=Hereditas |volume=155  |page=19  |publication-date=April 6, 2018|doi=10.1186/s41065-018-0057-5  |pmid=29636655  |pmc=5889524  |year=2018  }}</ref>。據估計，[[東京|東京]]周遭的日本人身上的[[繩文人|繩文血統]]約佔12%左右<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yomiuri.co.jp/fukayomi/20171214-OYT8T50003/|title=「縄文人」は独自進化したアジアの特異集団だった！: 深読み|date=2017-12-15|website=読売新聞オンライン|language=ja|access-date=2019-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417151409/https://www.yomiuri.co.jp/fukayomi/20171214-OYT8T50003/|archive-date=2019-04-17|url-status=live}}</ref>。Takashi et al. 2019確認現代日本人大多為彌生人後裔。在分析和比較過繩文人和現代日本人的線粒體DNA後，顯示繩文時代的人與[[古墳時代|古墳時代]]和[[平安時代|平安時代]]的人不存在連續性，而這項發現意味著日本人的基因轉換發生在古墳時代之前，或最起碼在稱名寺遺址所發現的是如此。<ref name="google272">David Blake Willis and Stephen Murphy-Shigematsu: [https://books.google.com/books?id=G2XPcHdz5DwC&pg=PA272 ''Transcultural Japan: At the Borderlands of Race, Gender and Identity,''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106021946/https://books.google.com/books?id=G2XPcHdz5DwC&pg=PA272 |date=2017-01-06 }}, p. 272: "“Wajin,” which is written with Chinese characters that can also be read “Yamato no hito” (Yamato person)".</ref>{{Quote|text=最近的研究透露繩文人和其他人口有別，包括現代日本人。|sign=Takahashi et al. 2019|source=(Adachi et al., 2011; Adachi and Nara, 2018)|title=}}另外一項2019年的研究分別指出現代日本人（大和民族）平均有90%左右的彌生人基因組，10%左右的繩文人基因組。<ref>{{cite web|title='Jomon woman' helps solve Japan's genetic mystery {{!}} NHK WORLD-JAPAN News|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/backstories/555/|website=NHK WORLD|access-date=2019-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611032509/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/backstories/555/|archive-date=2019-06-11|url-status=live}}</ref>。Gakuhari et al. 2019指出現代日本人的[[基因簇|基因簇]]與其他東亞族群最為接近，但與[[阿伊努人|阿伊努人]]有明顯差別。然而這份報告卻指出現代日本人只有3.3%繩文人基因<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Gakuhari|first1=Takashi|last2=Nakagome|first2=Shigeki|last3=Rasmussen|first3=Simon|last4=Allentoft|first4=Morten|last5=Sato|first5=Takehiro|last6=Korneliussen|first6=Thorfinn|last7=Chuinneagáin|first7=Blánaid|last8=Matsumae|first8=Hiromi|last9=Koganebuchi|first9=Kae|last10=Schmidt|first10=Ryan|last11=Mizushima|first11=Souichiro|date=March 15, 2019|orig-year=2019|title=Jomon genome sheds light on East Asian population history|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/biorxiv/early/2019/03/15/579177.full.pdf|publisher=[[bioRxiv|bioRxiv]]|publication-date=March 15, 2019|pages=3–5|journal=|access-date=2021-06-12|archive-date=2022-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220122052845/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/biorxiv/early/2019/03/15/579177.full.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> Kanazawa Kiriyama et al. 2019表示現代日本人有9-13%繩文人基因，而琉球人則有27%，並指他們都是彌生人<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/ase/advpub/0/advpub_190415/_pdf/-char/en |title=Late Jomon male and female genome sequences from the Funadomari site in Hokkaido, Japan - Hideaki Kanzawa-Kiriyama, Department of Anthropology, National Museum of Nature and Science 2018/2019en |access-date=2021-06-12 |archive-date=2021-04-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210425083308/https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/ase/advpub/0/advpub_190415/_pdf/-char/en |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

